Name: The Midnight Ride
Author: Qolore & TDarkShadow
Description: The Midnight Ride is a lite modlist that tries to stay as close as possible to vanilla, with some bugfixes and improvement of the performance, and add in some quality of life features without being intrusive. This modlist makes use of Lunar Fallout Overhaul.

State.Name: xSE PluginPreloader F4
State.Author: Kerber
State.Description: This mod allows preload F4SE plugins before the game initializes.

State.Name: Buffout 4
State.Author: Ryan
State.Description: It's like buffout but for the engine

State.Name: Better Coastal Waves - Wilder Water
State.Author: El Ha
State.Description: Some parts of the coast appear now wilder, by adding Far Harbor waves to it

State.Name: Shaikujin's Better warning for settlements being attacked
State.Author: Shaikujin
State.Description: Changes the 2 second message when a settlement is attacked to a standard message box (see screenshot).

State.Name: Clarity - A Visual Overhaul
State.Author: Bretton
State.Description: A zero performance loss, very subtle visual overhaul. Removes many annoying visuals in the game.

State.Name: Complex Vendors
State.Author: Zzyxzz
State.Description: Known from Skyrim and other games, many vendors are restricted. You can't sell everything to anyone. This also prevents the player from piling up currency. This mod applies several restrictions to several NPCs. For example, a doctor can only buy and sell chem related items. But there are still some stores, where you can dump everything.

State.Name: Decreased Automatron Bullshit Encounters and Minor Rust Devil Tweaks
State.Author: CptCOOTS
State.Description: Tweaks a few simple aspects of the Rust Devils. Random encounters with Rust Devils should be more rare. Added Robot Repair Kits to Rust Devil loot table. Added some creative names to Legendary Rust Devils.

State.Name: Extended Dialogue Interface
State.Author: reg2k and Neanka
State.Description: The Extended Dialogue Interface removes the hardcoded 4-option limit on dialogue and adds full engine support for any number of player dialogue options.

State.Name: Flicker Fixer
State.Author: Glass
State.Description: Fixes most of the exterior flickering aka z fighting in the game, particularly in the Boston and Cambridge areas.

Archives.Name: Fortune Finder 4 Fix - Basic Bottlecap Mine-43740-1-1-1583316002.7z

State.Name: Fortune Finder 4 Fix
State.Author: Whisper
State.Description:
An intense firefight, several opponents have exploded into caps. Money! Yay! Now that you're done, night's coming on and you've got to find the piles of caps spread all over...in the coming darkness...



...yeah screw that. Put those caps in my pocket, since you're that immersive and all. Same for them there Bottlecap Mines.

Archives.Name: FOV Slider and Player Height - ESL version-36768-1-3-1585132456.zip

State.Name: FOV Slider and Player Height
State.Author: g0kur
State.Description: Adjust FOVs/PlayerScale with sliders without messing up the Terminal Display and Pipboy.

State.Name: HUDFramework
State.Author: registrator2000
State.Description: HUDFramework is a UI framework that makes it possible for mods to add new UI elements to the HUD.

State.Name: Immersive HUD - iHUD
State.Author: Gopher
State.Description: HUD when you need. Hide when you don't.

State.Name: Interiors Enhanced - Darker Ambient Light and Fog
State.Author: fadingsignal
State.Description: Ambient light power and fog brightness inside all interiors reduced by 60%, without touching any directional light sources whatsoever, keeping lighting 100% true to vanilla except for those dark corners and unlit areas.  Subways are actually dark and scary!  Not just a filter, actual light data has been altered.  All-DLC covered.

State.Name: Previs Repair Pack
State.Author: BenRierimanu
State.Description: Basically BostonFPSFix but more up to date, but covers the entire game. Your one stop precombine shop.

State.Name: Kat's Power Armor Repair Kits
State.Author: Kaethela
State.Description: Originally designed to make perk requirements from Some Assembly Required visible, this mod lets you repair power armor using repair kits. Includes optional support for Creation Club and mod-added power armor. All ESL-flagged ESP files.

State.Name: Keep Radiants in the Commonwealth
State.Author: AlpineYJ
State.Description: This mod intends to keep all radiant quests assigned within the commonwealth - in the commonwealth. This means that Scribe Haylen won't be sending you to Far Harbor to retrieve the elusive BoogerTron device, and Mr. Tims won't be sending you to Nuka World to clear out raiders.  The real goal? You don't have to start any DLCs before you

State.Name: Laser weapons 1st person reposition
State.Author: akir4 and Wardaddy
State.Description: Makes the institute and standard laser weapons smaller in the 1st person.

State.Name: Lunar Fallout All in One Overhaul
State.Author: Moonracer
State.Description: Lunar Fallout is a comprehensive overhaul of Fallout 4 in a deceptively small package. This mod overhauls nearly every system in the game to work together and create a cohesive balanced experience. This aims to hit that sweet spot where you feel your character growing stronger and more capable, but the world continues to offer challenges.

State.Name: No Aggro Impact Landing (Power Armor)
State.Author: mm137
State.Description: Just makes the Impact Landing not turn friendly NPCs hostile

State.Name: Preston Garvey No Radiant Settlement Quests
State.Author: Wild1234
State.Description: Prevents Preston from giving you standard radiant quests after capturing the castle.

State.Name: Previs Repair Pack
State.Author: BenRierimanu
State.Description: Basically BostonFPSFix but more up to date, but covers the entire game. Your one stop precombine shop.

State.Name: RAW INPUT - The Ultimate Mouse Sensitivity Fix
State.Author: IceKK
State.Description: Disabled Mouse Acceleration, Horizontal/Vertical Parity, Scalable ADS Multiplier, Normalized Sensitivity

Archives.Name: RobCo Recon Scope Replacer - Main File-36374-1-03-1558554685.7z

State.Name: RobCo Recon Scope Replacer
State.Author: EmeraldReign
State.Description: Replaces the vanilla Recon Scope for each weapon with a brand new asset with custom models, textures and materials.

State.Name: Salvage Beacons
State.Author: kinggath
State.Description: Put your settlers to work carrying all your loot back to your settlements so you can focus on saving the Commonwealth.

State.Name: Survival Saving - Holotapes save the game
State.Author: DeEz
State.Description: Adds a lore-friendly way of saving in the new Survival mode. Now with an ingame configurator!

State.Name: True Invisibility Redux
State.Author: Sensei Shisha
State.Description: Completely overhauls the stealth fields in Fallout 4. Now you can switch it on and off on the fly, see the remaining duration on a HUD widget, and most importantly, the enemies finally won't see you from miles away. Requires MCM and HUDFramework.

State.Name: Unofficial Fallout 4 Patch
State.Author: Unofficial Patch Project Team
State.Description: A comprehensive bugfixing mod for Fallout 4. The goal of the Unofficial Fallout 4 Patch (aka UFO4P) is to eventually fix every bug with Fallout 4 not officially resolved by the developers to the limits of the Creation Kit and community-developed tools, in one easy-to-install package.

State.Name: FO4Edit
State.Author: ElminsterAU and the xEdit Team
State.Description: FO4Edit is the Fallout 4 version of xEdit. xEdit is an advanced graphical module viewer/editor and conflict detector.

State.Name: Bullet Counted Reload System (BCR)
State.Author: shavkacagarikia
State.Description: Finally, a proper engine-level system for bullet counted reloads with most of the features such a system should have.

State.Name: Bullet Counted Reload System (BCR)
State.Author: shavkacagarikia
State.Description: Finally, a proper engine-level system for bullet counted reloads with most of the features such a system should have.

State.Name: DEF_UI Iconlibs Rescaled and Fixed
State.Author: Phlunder
State.Description: Aims to bring consistency in design and coloring to the icon library. Also fixes various issues with icon sizes, bounding boxes, and scaling.

State.Name: HUDFramework
State.Author: registrator2000
State.Description: HUDFramework is a UI framework that makes it possible for mods to add new UI elements to the HUD.

State.Name: Mod Configuration Menu
State.Author: reg2k - Neanka - shadowslasher410
State.Description: The Mod Configuration Menu is a settings page for mods! It provides a central location for mod configuration, accessible via the Pause menu.

Archives.Name: No More Power Armor Battery Pathing-33080-1-0.7z

State.Name: No PA Battery Pathing
State.Author: John Doe Bowler
State.Description: Removes the forced loss of control / buggy pathing that happens every time you insert a Fusion Core in a Power Armor.

State.Name: Ruddy88's Simple Sorter
State.Author: Ruddy88
State.Description: Simple Sorter is a FO4Edit script that will automatically add the text needed for icon replacements for all valid items in your entire load order. It automatically scans your mod list, loads all valid items to a new ESP, then detects what sort of item it is so that the correct icons are used. No more patches, no more manually patching.

State.Name: MXPF - Mator's xEdit Patching Framework
State.Author: Mator
State.Description: This is an API framework for xEdit scripts for creating patches.  MXPF offers a high performance solution that greatly simplifies creating xEdit scripts for patch generation.  Even if you've never programmed before, you'll find the MXPF framework is easy to learn to and use.

State.Name: Ruddy88's Simple Sorter

It automatically scans your mod list, loads all valid items to a new ESP, then detects what sort of item it is so that the correct icons are used. No more patches, no more manually patching.

State.Name: Crafting Highlight Fix
State.Author: registrator2000
State.Description:
A F4SE plugin that allows you to disable the hardcoded, vision-obscuring shader effect at various workbenches so you can actually see what you're crafting.



Also allows you to change the shader effect for the Power Armor station and robot workbenches to a outline-only shader instead of a full shader.

Untie the game speed from the framerate. Fixes physical bugs. Reduces loading time.

Now there is a separate version for VR.

State.Author: mluppov

Fixed twitching/stuttering when sprinting in first person.

State.Description: This is a F4SE plugin which restores some hard-coded features disabled by game in survival mode,for example,unlock console,enable TGM,enable fast travel,restore vanilla compass settings,enalbe quick save and auto save,etc .
